### Login - obter token JWT
POST http://localhost:8080/academics/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Guarda o token na variável @token para usar nos próximos requests
# Resposta esperada: {"token": "eyJhbGc..."}

###

### GET protegido - com token válido (ADMIN)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzM4NCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhZG1pbiIsInVzZXJJZCI6MSwicm9sZSI6IkFETUlOSVNUUkFET1IiLCJpYXQiOjE3NjQ3MTEwODQsImV4cCI6MTc2NDcxNDY4NH0.ElQ9TxoQVTk2KfPgpZ_jNwcxKu8M3WMLirLdp-oJ34hH6p5-ucluxOIxot0AXMAo

###

### GET protegido - SEM token (deve falhar com 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users

###

### GET protegido - com token INVÁLIDO (deve falhar com 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###

### GET protegido - com Bearer format errado (deve falhar com 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users
Authorization: InvalidToken

###

### GET público - @PermitAll (funciona sem token)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/public/health

###

### GET negado a todos - @DenyAll (deve falhar com 403)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/admin/restricted

###

### POST com role específica - USER (deve falhar com 403 se tiver ADMIN)
POST http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users/create
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzM4NCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhZG1pbiIsInVzZXJJZCI6MSwicm9sZSI6IkFETUlOSVNUUkFET1IiLCJpYXQiOjE3NjQ3MTEwODQsImV4cCI6MTc2NDcxNDY4NH0.ElQ9TxoQVTk2KfPgpZ_jNwcxKu8M3WMLirLdp-oJ34hH6p5-ucluxOIxot0AXMAo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "role": "USER"
}

###

### Teste de expiração - token expirado (deve falhar com 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzM4NCJ9.eyJleHAiOjE2OTg3NjUwMDB9.expired...

